See and the Society of Jesus for many years. This book, the fruit of a major conference on the history, nature, and dynamics of relations between Jesuits and contemporary Jewish life, brings together a rich, wide-ranging selection of essays by Jesuit scholars and pastoral leaders, a leading Jewish studies scholar, and a leading rabbi. Drawing on a variety of approaches in historical and constructive theology, literary criticism, and spirituality, the contributors explore historical, philosophical, theological, cultural, and institutional themes—from Ignatian perspectives on Halakhic spirituality and the role played in Jesuit history by Jews forced to convert to Christianity to Jesuit perspectives on Hannah Arendt, Abraham Joshua Heschel, and Harold Bloom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh1 aBen-Chorin, Rabbi Tovia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernauer, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDu Brul, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasimow, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMichel, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuhaus, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aObirek, Stanisław, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRastoin, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRutishauser, Christian M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSonnet, Jean-Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Pre